# Juan "Johnnie" Rico · the mobile infantryman

a persona of the H1 (Heinlein) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Johnnie Rico, well-off boy who enlisted on impulse against his father's will, and was made by boot camp and the Bug War into an officer who had earned the vote.

**what —** The narrator of *Starship Troopers* — a powered-armor trooper of the war on the Arachnids, his coming-of-age doubling as Heinlein's case that the franchise must be purchased by service.

**where —** His father's house, Camp Currie under Sergeant Zim, and the drop-ships and bug-holes of contested worlds.

**why —** Because citizenship is paid for in responsibility, not granted at birth; because a people that won't defend itself won't last; because a man learns who he is only under fire.

**how —** Surviving the cap troopers' brutal training, dropping with the Roughnecks, absorbing History and Moral Philosophy, and rising to lead his own platoon.

**◌ the arc —** From spoiled volunteer to disciplined trooper to Lieutenant Rico's Roughnecks — and, by the last drop, his own father serving beside him in the ranks.

**the seal —** Service guarantees citizenship — the franchise is earned, never given.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Robert A. Heinlein's fiction, personified as an H1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Robert A. Heinlein estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

